-161425"/><CodeA name="root" value="re:usa"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="0"/></CodeI></Code></CSet><CSet fid="ns"><Code value="gart"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Art</CodeD><CodeI org="rbc" action="add"><CodeA name="rule" value="824583"/><CodeA name="db" value="prbc---00018581-20180324-194406"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="2"/></CodeI></Code><Code value="gcat"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Political/General News</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="root" value="ns:gart"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="0"/></CodeI></Code><Code value="gent"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Arts/Entertainment</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="root" value="ns:gart"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001001-20180324-161425"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="1"/></CodeI></Code></CSet></CodeSets><DescTPC fid="de"><DescField fid="ipd">T: Design Magazine </DescField></DescTPC></MetadataPT><ArchiveDoc xml:space="preserve"><Article markup="pp0" lang="en" index="field"><HandL fid="hlp"><Title fid="hl"><SectionName fid="se" index="field">T: Design Magazine; SECTM2</SectionName><ColumnName fid="clm" index="field"></ColumnName><Headline fid="hd"><Para lang="en">Behind the Story</Para></Headline></Title><LeadPara fid="lp"><Para>Creating interiors stories can be quite invasive for our subjects -- photographers shooting the most private details of their homes, writers asking the kind of meddling questions only close friends and therapists dare ask. Such was the case with our cover story (TIME'S ARROW, Page 152), where the photographer Simon Watson, his assistant and I descended upon Schloss Hollenegg -- an Austrian castle that is the home of Alice Liechtenstein, who also curates an annual design exhibition and residency there -- in the hope of leaving two days later with images of most of the home's 52 rooms.</Para><Para>Fortunately, Alice and her husband, Alfred, took the intrusion in stride and even made us feel like welcome guests, to the point where we were invited to celebrate Alfred's 45th birthday with the family at a local restaurant. I was put up in the room where the designers usually stay, the one covered in the magnificent pale pink Chinese wallpaper you see on the cover.</Para></LeadPara></HandL><TailParas fid="td"><Para>The family cat was less welcoming. One day during lunch, he sauntered through the dining room toward the room where I was staying, almost unnoticed. Just before he slipped from sight, he glanced over his shoulder and looked me in the eye. I was sure he was up to no good, so as soon as lunch was finished I went to my room, to discover he had marked his territory by urinating in my suitcase.</Para><Para>After a flurry of apologies, Alice had all my belongings cleaned, but the cat's point had been made. The next morning at 4 a.m., as I slipped out the door to catch my cab to the airport, he dashed into the house. I was just a visitor here, but this was his home. -- Tom Delavan</Para><Para>This is a more complete version of the story than the one that appeared in print.</Para></TailParas><Byline fid="by" index="field">By TOM DELAVAN </Byline><Credit fid="cr" index="field"></Credit><Contact fid="ct" index="field"></Contact><Notes fid="rf" index="field"></Notes><Art fid="art" index="field">The ''blue room'' of Schloss Hollenegg, named for its 19th-century velvet brocade walls. (PHOTOGRAPH BY SIMON WATSON) </Art><Copyright fid="cy" index="field">Copyright 2018 The New York Times Company.  All Rights Reserved. </Copyright></Article></ArchiveDoc><AdocTOC adoctype="article"><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/ArchiveDoc::Article" type="arttext"></Item><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/InvertText" type="invtext"></Item></AdocTOC></DistDoc>

